    "markdown_debrief": "### SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n> **💡 BIRADS: Your breast's report card, guiding its fate!**\n\n---\n\n## S — Set the Stage\nBIRADS is a standardized system for reporting mammography, ultrasound, and MRI findings. The correct answer, \"Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System,\" accurately reflects its purpose in classifying breast lesions and guiding management.\n\n## H — Highlight Excellence\nThe Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System (BIRADS) was developed by the American College of Radiology (ACR) to standardize breast imaging reports and facilitate communication among radiologists, referring physicians, and patients. It provides a universal lexicon for describing findings and assigns a category from 0 to 6, each with specific management recommendations. This standardization reduces ambiguity, improves patient care by ensuring appropriate follow-up or biopsy, and aids in research and quality assurance.\n\n## A — Address the Gaps\n\nOption B (Incorrect): \"Best Imaging Reporting and Data System\" is incorrect as \"Best\" is not the correct first word; the system is specific to \"Breast\" imaging.\nOption C (Incorrect): \"Brain Imaging Reporting and data system\" is incorrect as BIRADS is exclusively for breast imaging, not brain imaging.\nOption D (Incorrect): \"Best imaging reporting and data system\" is incorrect for the same reason as Option B; \"Best\" is not the correct term, and the system is specific to \"Breast\".\n\n## R — Review Learning Points\n\n| Acronym | Full Form | Purpose | Key Categories/Scores |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| BIRADS | Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System | Standardizes breast imaging reports (mammography, US, MRI) and management recommendations. | 0 (Incomplete), 1 (Negative), 2 (Benign), 3 (Probably Benign), 4 (Suspicious), 5 (Highly Suggestive of Malignancy), 6 (Known Biopsy-Proven Malignancy) |\n| TIRADS | Thyroid Imaging Reporting and Data System | Standardizes thyroid nodule ultrasound reports and risk stratification for malignancy. | TR1-TR5 (based on features like composition, echogenicity, shape, margin, echogenic foci) |\n| LI-RADS | Liver Imaging Reporting and Data System | Standardizes reporting and data collection for liver lesions in patients at risk for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC). | LR1-LR5 (based on imaging features and size, indicating probability of HCC) |\n| PI-RADS | Prostate Imaging Reporting and Data System | Standardizes prostate MRI interpretation and risk stratification for clinically significant prostate cancer. | PIRADS 1-5 (based on T2W, DWI, DCE sequences) |\n\n## P — Plan (Board Pearl)\nBoard Pearl: BIRADS is for Breast, not Best or Brain.\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Imaging & Intraoperative Pearl\nOn mammography, ultrasound, or MRI, a BIRADS category is assigned to each breast lesion. For example, a BIRADS 4 lesion requires biopsy, while a BIRADS 2 lesion is benign and requires no further action.\n\n## 📋 Guideline Anchor\nAmerican College of Radiology (ACR) BIRADS Atlas, 5th Edition (2013). It provides comprehensive guidelines for breast imaging interpretation and reporting.\n\n---\n\n### Answer Breakdown\n| Option | Text | Status |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| A | Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System | ✅ Correct |\n| B | Best Imaging Reporting and Data System | ❌ Incorrect |\n| C | Brain Imaging Reporting and data system | ❌ Incorrect |\n| D | Best imaging reporting and data system | ❌ Incorrect |\n\n**✅ Answer: A) Breast Imaging Reporting and Data System** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Difficulty: Easy** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Source: Surgery Essence**\n",
